00:34:26,544 --> 00:34:29,386
the books or hover your cursor over the books until something happens.

562
00:34:30,086 --> 00:34:33,688
And at best, this is very frustrating.

563
00:34:35,509 --> 00:34:37,409
Your player is just brute force clicking around.

564
00:34:37,470 --> 00:34:40,851
They're not thinking about the connections between the objects that they're looking at.

565
00:34:40,891 --> 00:34:42,872
They're just kind of clicking mindlessly.

566
00:34:44,033 --> 00:34:47,554
At worst, your player doesn't see that this is a puzzle at all and skips it.

567
00:34:48,295 --> 00:34:51,317
So it's only important to message your clues, but also

568
00:34:51,377 --> 00:34:52,858
message your puzzle in general.

569
00:34:56,381 --> 00:34:58,442
So props aren't the only way, of course, to

570
00:34:59,243 --> 00:35:00,043
message your puzzles.

